item.title: TED: 'A sci-fi vision of love from a 318-year-old hologram | Monica Byrne'
item.description:
Science fiction writer Monica Byrne imagines rich worlds populated with characters who defy our racial, social and gender stereotypes. In this performance, Byrne appears as a hologram named Pilar, transmitting a story of love and loss back to us from a near future when humans have colonized the universe. "It's always funny what you think the future is going to be like versus what it turns out to be," she says.

TEDTalks is a daily video podcast of the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world's leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and much more.

Find closed captions and translated subtitles in many languages at http://www.ted.com/translate

item.title: CoryxKenshin: 'Nearly DIED From Car Accident Yesterday.. (Driving With Sleep Deprivation/Drowsiness PSA)'
item.description:
I feel so bad, I'm just extremely remorseful for putting lives other than my own in jeopardy. Driving back home from an amusement, my friend Brandon and I got into the most dangerous situation of our lives. If you are driving and are sleepy or anything of the like, PLEASE pull over. In our case, we were fortunate enough to come out unharmed. But it could've been a lot worse, I just thank God that it wasn't. So while you have the chance, pull over and get the rest you need, lest you might not get the chance if you're too late.

Some facts about driving sleepy/drowsy that I feel you should know: http://drowsydriving.org/about/facts-and-stats/
